cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with object segmentation from RGB-D images, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The proposed approach is based on graph partitioning and does not rely on machine learning or image features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper is specifically focused on robotic grasping, it is also likely to belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The use of cost functions and graph partitioning also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) due to its use of edge detection and depth information.
